\â€˜But Socrates rarely washed.'

Why, his body was clean and bright, nay, it was so gracious and agreeable that
the handsomest and noblest were in love with him, and desired to recline by
him rather than by those who were perfect in beauty. He might have never washed
or bathed, if he had liked; I tell you his ablutions, if rare, were powerful.
